<h2 id=3D"file-storage---how-to-save/open/delete-file?" class=3D"StyledHead=
ing-sc-1rdh4aw-0 dxYuao">4. File Storage - How to Save/Open/Delete File?</h=
2>
<p class=3D"StyledParagraph-sc-tbetod-0 ggSFeD">By default, all inputs with=
 the most recent status are saved in your browser's storage. As a result, y=
ou will be able to access the same data the next time you visit using the s=
ame browser.
<i>*Please keep in mind that if you clean your browser's history or your br=
owser's memory becomes overloaded, the data may be lost.</i></p>
<p class=3D"StyledParagraph-sc-tbetod-0 ggSFeD">You can save more lists to =
the Picker Wheel cloud storage. This only applies to logged-in users. Signi=
ng up for an account is free. Click the menu button (top right of the page)=
 and sign up.
<span class=3D"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style=3D"position:relative;displa=
y:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;max-width:199px">
      <span class=3D"gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style=3D"padding-b=
ottom:21.311475409836063%;position:relative;bottom:0;left:0;background-imag=
